review_blob: Drinking from bottle. Excellent hop smell and taste. Very nice amber color. Lovely Red Ale from Rogue.
beer_name: Rogue Dry Hopped St. Rogue Red Ale

review_blob: Consistent foam with beautiful deep amber color. Malty flavor which balances bitterness. Although 8.5 abv, nice complex flavor.
Draft one at Barbarium Beer Pub. Persistent foam. A nice light pale yellow color. Great go flavor at the end.

Copper color and foam with good density. Lovely hop flavor while drinking it and the cocoa smell and taste is so smooth and pleasant. 

Its summer time here in Brazil and having the chance to drink it from the growler is a gift from heaven. So nice to drink it in this hot sunny weather. 

Thank you Mr Koch and Mr Cavalcanti for this great beer. Love it!
Creamy foam and copper color. Nice balance between malt and hop flavours. Since its hot weather here in Brazil, its a good call.
